17
00:01:07,610 --> 00:01:11,930
And the main principle of these dependencies is dependency rule.

18
00:01:11,960 --> 00:01:17,660
As we already seen in the dependency inversion principle, there is a dependency rule, and this rule

19
00:01:17,660 --> 00:01:22,100
says that source code dependencies can only point inwards.

20
00:01:22,100 --> 00:01:28,880
Here you can see that source code dependencies can only point the inwards, and the inner circle can

21
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:31,130
know anything at all about something.

22
00:01:31,130 --> 00:01:37,640
In outer circle only implementation, those of abstractions will become external outer layers.

23
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:44,150
So this is the dependency rule that we can see different implementation and illustration of dependencies.

24
00:01:44,150 --> 00:01:50,600
And these will be pointing inwards always because domain layers implement the business logic with the

